Ad Text:
A leading organisation in Melbourne is seeking a Senior Business Analyst to join their Retail Enterprise Platform Delivery team, focusing on finance enablement for billing policy and claims. This role offers you the chance to work at the intersection of technology and business, acting as a vital bridge between technical teams, testers, and business stakeholders. You will be empowered to facilitate requirements gathering and drive end-to-end solutions.

What you'll do:

As a Senior Business Analyst you will play a pivotal role in shaping the future of enterprise finance systems on the Retail Enterprise Platform Delivery team. Your day-to-day responsibilities will centre around facilitating effective communication between business units focused on billing policy and claims enablement, as well as technical teams responsible for implementing solutions. You will be instrumental in driving requirements from initial conception through to successful delivery, ensuring that every stakeholder's voice is heard and integrated into the final product. By leveraging your expertise in finance operations - particularly monthly processing tasks-and your familiarity with SAP ERP environments, you will help streamline processes while maintaining compliance with corporate disclosure standards.

Facilitate comprehensive requirements gathering sessions with both business stakeholders and technical teams to ensure clarity and alignment throughout project lifecycles.
Act as the primary conduit between finance operations and IT delivery teams, translating complex business needs into actionable technical specifications.
Lead workshops and meetings that encourage open communication, co-operation, and consensus among diverse groups including testers, developers, and business users.
Support monthly processing activities by ensuring system enhancements align with accounting operations such as general ledger management, accounts payable, and accounts receivable.

What you bring:

The ideal candidate for the Senior Business Analyst - Finance position will bring substantial experience in managing core finance functions such as monthly processing cycles, chartered account activities, general ledger oversight, AP/AR transactions, and related accounting operations. Your background should include hands-on exposure to SAP ERP platforms-especially within Financial Accounting modules-enabling you to understand both system capabilities and user requirements. Beyond technical proficiency, your success will hinge on your ability to connect with people: building rapport across departments; facilitating open dialogue; documenting needs accurately; and guiding teams toward shared solutions.

Finance operations expertise across month-end processing, GL, AP/AR, and SAP ERP (Financial Accounting modules)

Strong stakeholder and facilitation skills, able to lead workshops, elicit requirements, and build consensus across business and technical teams

Clear communicator and documenter, translating complex processes into structured artefacts for varied audiences

Reliable delivery mindset, supporting large enterprise programs with professionalism, empathy, and proactive problem-solving

What's next:

If you are ready to take the next step in your career as a Senior Business Analyst - Finance within an environment that values collaboration, inclusivity, and professional development, we encourage you to apply now!

Apply today by clicking on the link below - don't miss out on this exciting opportunity!

Why Sparke Helmore?

As an independent Australian firm with a long history and a big heart, we have a rich story to tell. Our spirit is built on the power of relationships with our people, clients and communities.

At Sparke Helmore, you’ll be actively involved as part of a diverse, genuine and friendly team. We’ll help you harness your ambition and take your skills to new heights with exposure to outstanding clients and easy access to exceptional leaders and mentors.

Your story is yours to define. We’d like to be part of it and for you to be part of ours.

Due to growth, we have an exciting opportunity for a Senior Transformation Consultant (Operational Excellence) to join our Sydney office.

About the role and about the team

The Senior Transformation Consultant will support the Director of Operational Excellence in identifying, leading, and implementing optimisation strategies, including integrating and scaling the use of emerging AI technologies to improve operational efficiency, resource utilisation, and overall business performance. This role plays a critical part in driving continuous improvement, identifying opportunities for optimisation, embracing emerging technologies, and fostering a culture of excellence across the firm.

Your key responsibilities will include:

Assist in the baselining, evaluation, and redesign of business processes to enhance efficiency and effectiveness. Support the implementation of process improvement initiatives.

Collaborate with Partners, legal teams, and business services teams to gather information, understand their needs, and provide insights to support decision-making. Maintain strong relationships with key stakeholders.

Maintain comprehensive documentation of process, procedures, and project outcomes. Ensure all documentation is up-to-date and accessible.  

Promote a culture of continuous improvement by identifying opportunities for optimisation and innovation. Monitor and analyse success metrics for completed projects to identify opportunities for process improvements and drive a continuous improvement cycle.

Assist in the discovery, application, and change management approach in support of the appropriate adoption of emerging technologies across the firm in support of uplifting operational performance.

This is a newly created role which will offer a broad and diverse scope of work. You will have the opportunity to work directly with Partners, legal teams, and colleagues across the firm, making this a standout opportunity for a process improvement specialist looking to progress their career, build visibility, and refine their stakeholder engagement capabilities in a dynamic environment. It is a standalone position which will have exceptional external support, as well as support from internal business services lines.

About you

At least 5 years’ experience in transformation, process improvement or a similar role. Law firm or professional services experience working with senior stakeholders (Partners and legal teams) is essential.

Experience running both in person and remote workshops to elicit business requirements from a nationally dispersed group of stakeholders is essential.

Ability to capture business requirements and create associated documentation for business approval.

Ability to translate business requirements into technical implementation stories for development.

Knowledge of the application of emerging AI technologies in the workplace such as RPA, Machine Learning and Large Language Models.

Proficiency in data analysis tools and software such as Excel, SQL, Tableau, Power BI.

Knowledge of process improvement methodologies such as Lean, Six Sigma, Kaizen.

Experience with project management tools and methodologies such as MS Project, MS Planner, Jira, Confluence, Prince2, and Agile Scrum.

What Sparke Helmore can offer you

Our culture is one which values and celebrates diversity to better represent the communities in which we live and work. We encourage people from all backgrounds to join us - and bring their whole selves to work.

We recognise people value things differently. That's why our comprehensive benefits program is wide ranging so that everyone can find something that appeals to them. We're sure you will find something to love about what Sparke Helmore has to offer.

To find out more about what is on offer at Sparke Helmore please visit our website: https://www.sparke.com.au/join-us/why-sparke-helmore/

We believe the best stories are shared.

We’ve been proudly serving Australian communities since 1914 and have grown to become a top 30-listed company on the ASX with a portfolio of iconic homegrown brands. At the heart of our continued success is over 115,000 team members working across the country, all contributing to bringing our customers smiles. You’ll not only get to see your work make a difference, you’ll be part of a team working together to help Australians eat and live better every day.

About the team

Our Finance team are a vital partner in every aspect of our business, providing commercial insights to drive our success and influence everything we do. With presence in every department, we analyse performance, and deliver actionable insights that shape our strategic decisions.

About the role


As part of a highly visible team, you’ll play a critical role in driving business decision-making and ensuring alignment across the organisation. This position is central to delivering the planning cycle and supporting strategic initiatives that shape the future of the business. Your responsibilities will include:



Facilitate and deliver the business planning cycle, ensuring alignment across all parts of the business.
Support business-wide planning processes including budget and multi-year strategic planning.
Ensure delivery of Board and Executive Leadership team requirements and decision-making information, providing accurate insights.
Drive Coles Group planning processes liaising with wider finance team and strategy on deliverables & timelines.
Work as a team player, influencing, coaching and engaging across the business and within the team to drive continuous improvements across planning systems and processes and enhance system usage.

About you and your skills

You’ll bring strong financial expertise and a collaborative approach to problem-solving. Your ability to manage complex data, build relationships, and influence stakeholders will be key to success in this role. As the successful candidate, you will have:



CA/CPA qualified in addition to finance background preferably covering financial control, FP&A or commercial decision support.
Finance experience in a retail or FMCG environment desirable.
Understanding of standard financial KPIs across the P&L, balance sheet and cash flow.
Ability to establish relationships and cross-functional partnerships across the business.
Strong stakeholder management skills including influencing & negotiating.
Strong communication & presentation skills (verbal and written), ability to present simplified complex data & concepts to enable decision making.
Strong time management and planning skills, ability to manage multiple priorities in a high-pressure environment.

What’s in it for you?

Flexible working options: We know that work is only one part of your life, so we actively encourage a positive work-life balance and provide hybrid working options to help you achieve it.
Office perks: Take advantage of our gym facility and fitness classes, free parking, BBQ area, mini-Coles supermarket, fooderie hub where you can sample new products before they hit the shelves, school holiday program and so much more when you come in.
Discounts: Eligible team members receive 5% discount all year round on your Supermarket and Liquor online and in-store purchases. We also offer additional periods of double discount (10%) at various times throughout the year. As well as hotdeals exclusive to team members that translate into additional savings.
Reward through recognition: Give and receive recognition, linked to our Coles values, through our digital recognition platform ‘mythanks’. You can accumulate points to redeem in the online shop for exciting gifts and electronic gift cards from an extensive range of retailers.
Opportunities for learning and development: No matter where you start within our diverse business, you’ll have experiences, exposure, and education to satisfy you. Discover and explore a variety of career development programs and job-specific training.
Paid parental leave: We understand how important your life outside work is and offer permanent team members paid parental leave to support you in balancing work and family.
Investment in your future: Our annual team member share plan offer allows eligible team members to make regular pre-tax salary sacrifice deductions to purchase Coles Group shares.

About the recruitment process

We’re continuing to build a gender equitable team, and a culture that is just as diverse, inclusive and welcoming as the communities we serve. We are committed to creating a workplace that is safe and respectful for our team. We encourage applications from people of all ages, cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), abilities, sexual orientation and gender identities.

We’re happy to adjust our recruitment process to support candidates with disability. For further information and additional contact details visit the ‘Our Recruitment Process’ section of our careers site or email inclusionrecruitment@coles.com.au

Principal Strategic Business Consultant - Permanent Full Time - Perth CBD





Western Power is a government-owned utility responsible for planning, building and operating Western Australia's electricity network, playing a critical role in enabling the state's energy transition and major decarbonisation initiatives.

This role operates as a trusted advisor to the Head of Engineering and Design, and the selected candidate will join as a member of the leadership team of this large engineering function.

This is high-impact strategic role suited for a seasoned consulting professional seeking to transition from advisory to leadership influence within a critical infrastructure organisation. We are looking for strategic experience in the rapid diagnosis of complex operating model issues and translating insight into clear, executive-ready advice.

When issues arise or opportunities emerge, the role conducts targeted analysis of financial, operational, and workforce data to identify root causes and develop practical, executive-ready recommendations. Working closely with senior leaders across Western Power, the role shapes executive communications, drives targeted business improvements, and delivers measurable outcomes. The role is focused on practical execution, pace, and delivering measurable business impact.

Your Role in Action

Develop high-impact executive presentations and decision-making packs; collect and synthesise complex data to support strategic recommendations and business storytelling.
Facilitate strategic planning workshops, contribute to board papers and business cases, and translate business strategy into actionable initiatives with clear success criteria.
Collaborate with stakeholders to define and refine enterprise project, program, and portfolio management frameworks that enhance organisational maturity and delivery capability.
Identify, manage, and deliver functional improvement projects within Engineering and Design, ensuring timely execution and adherence to budget.
Conduct regular, data-driven analysis of functional performance to uncover risks and opportunities, champion innovation and continuous improvement to foster a culture of excellence.
Design and implement KPIs, monitoring systems, and reporting frameworks aligned with organisational strategy to support functional excellence.
Identify relevant performance benchmarks by developing a network with other leading utilities around the world.
Provide timely and insightful reporting of research findings, analysis, and business intelligence to support informed decision-making.
Serve as a key liaison for triaging operational queries and enabling leadership to focus on strategic, high-value initiatives.
Partner with other senior leaders across the business to align work allocation and commercial activities with operational priorities and organisational goals.
Share technical knowledge and mentor leadership team to build internal capability to foster professional growth and industry knowledge through ongoing learning.
Enhance the corporate reputation of Engineering & Design through consistent delivery of high-quality outcomes and stakeholder engagement.
Provide subject matter expertise and advanced analytical support, including gap analysis, high-level scoping, and strategic advisory to enable data-driven decision-making.
Translate business strategy into clearly defined initiatives, articulating success criteria and establishing robust performance measurement frameworks (financial and non-financial).
Develop own capabilities by participating in assessment and development planning activities as well as formal and informal training and coaching; gain or maintain external professional accreditation, where relevant, to improve performance and fulfill personal potential.

What Makes You a Great Fit

Degree qualified in Business Administration, Management, Project Management, Finance or related discipline.
A seasoned consulting professional with broad and deep expertise in strategy, business transformation, and operations, complemented by exceptional analytical and storytelling capabilities to translate complex ideas into clear, compelling narratives.
Demonstrated experience and skills in delivering client quality outputs.
Strong skills in using Microsoft PowerPoint.
Strong ability to manage business risks and uncover growth opportunities.
Significant expertise in internal and external stakeholder relations, demonstrating capability to persuade and influence strategic outcomes.

By joining Western Power, you will contribute to powering a cleaner energy future. We are dedicated to fostering career development and promoting a healthy work-life balance, empowering you to drive innovation as we develop a network that will serve the Western Australian community for generations. You will also benefit from a range of perks and opportunities, including:

Over 50% of our employment opportunities are driven by career progression.
Flexible work arrangements to support part time work, working hours and working from home arrangements.
The opportunity to purchase up to four weeks of additional leave per year.
Access to salary packaging, social club activities, and discounted health insurance and gym membership.
An award-winning employee recognition and benefits programme.
An innovative team culture that's enabling the transition to renewable energy and decarbonisation.  
In addition to standard leave, enjoy three wellness leave days each year.
Access to end-of-trip facilities at our Perth office and South Metro Depot, perfect for cyclists.
22 weeks paid parental leave and 5 days of First Nations cultural leave to support family and cultural connections.

Applications close on 23 January 2026.

We value diversity and inclusivity, encouraging applications from all backgrounds, including women, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, and LGBTQIA+ communities. As a WORK180-endorsed employer for women, we are proud of our commitment to inclusion. You can learn more about this through our Reconciliation Action Plan and Disability Access and Inclusion Plan.

Learn more about Western Power here: About (westernpower.com.au)

The role

This role sits at the heart of how technology risk data is captured, governed and turned into meaningful insight. You’ll own and optimise our enterprise GRC system, ensuring it’s reliable, well-governed and genuinely useful for the business.

Operating in a Line 2 capacity, you’ll work closely with technology and risk stakeholders to uplift reporting, strengthen data integrity, and provide thoughtful challenge across key technology risk areas. It’s a hands-on role with real influence, ideal for someone who enjoys blending systems, data and risk expertise.

 

Position Accountabilities 

In this role, you will:

Own the day-to-day management and optimisation of the enterprise GRC platform
Manage system configuration, user access, workflows and data structures
Act as the go-to expert for GRC system queries, enhancements and issue resolution
Strengthen data quality through controls, validation checks and reconciliation processes
Support integrations and data movements between risk systems and broader enterprise platforms
Provide second-line oversight and challenge across technology and data risk practices
Contribute to reviews, audits and control assurance activities within Technology Risk
Develop strong system reporting and insights that support risk decision-making

 

What experience you’ll bring

You’ll bring a mix of technical capability, risk awareness and stakeholder confidence, including:

Experience working in data, reporting, analytics or systems roles within risk, compliance or technology environments
Hands-on exposure to GRC platforms (RSA Archer or similar highly regarded)
Strong grounding in data quality, governance, lineage and control concepts
Familiarity with technology risk, data risk or enterprise risk frameworks in regulated environments
Confidence working with reporting and analysis tools such as Power BI, BigQuery or SQL
A practical mindset, comfortable balancing detail with commercial outcomes
Relevant qualifications in IT, business, finance or a related discipline


Location –Toowong

Close to a variety of public transport and easy parking options, the Toowong office has excellent end of trip facilities (including secure bike storage and showers), outdoor spaces and plenty of modern collaborative areas to work and connect with colleagues. 

Conveniently based at Toowong Village tower with views of the mountains and the Brisbane River, our location is only 4 km from the city and provides access to retail, restaurants and other amenities.

 

The benefits of working at A&G

Be rewarded - we recognise high performance and reward our people for their hard work through bonuses and other perks.
Work flexibility - with options to work from home up to two days per week.
Options for leave - life happens, so we’ve got volunteer days, an additional paid ‘ME’ day, paid parental leave and the opportunity to purchase additional leave to cover all of the big stuff.
Grow with us - we’ve got learning and professional development opportunities to suit everyone.
Give back - our A&G Difference program gives you the power to change our community for the better through volunteering, fundraising and donation opportunities for causes that you’re passionate about.
Take care of yourself - your wellbeing is important to us and our healthy mind and body hub, mental-health support and fitness discounts will help you be your best self.
Celebrate the wins - we love sharing our successes and celebrating together - join us and you’ve got a ticket to our many on-site events throughout the year, family fun days and annual celebrations.
Save money - as well as discounts on insurance products, we’ve teamed up with some incredible retailers, hospitality providers and others to bring you discounts on your purchases, no matter where you are in Australia.

 

About us

Auto & General (A&G) is the fastest-growing major Motor and Home insurer in Australia, providing insurance products and solutions to safeguard a brighter future for our customers and community.  

Our range of general insurance products including Car, Motorcycle, Home, Contents Pet and Travel products are delivered through our multi-award-winning brand Budget Direct and partnerships with leading brands - ING, Qantas, Virgin Money and Coles Insurance.

We’re excited about the future and we’re always on the lookout for talented, passionate individuals who can help us achieve our goal of being Australia’s best insurer! If this sounds like you, apply today.

 

Auto & General values individual differences and believes in fostering an inclusive culture that creates a great place to work for all.

Wirrigan is seeking a Senior Policy & Economic Analyst (Level 9/10) to support a major government program undertaking a business case update in response to an ERC callback.

This is a high-impact role requiring strong quantitative and financial analysis skills, combined with the ability to translate financial impacts into clear policy advice for senior decision-makers. You will work closely with financial modellers, program leaders and governance forums to assess the impacts of policy, design and assumption changes within an approved funding envelope.

Key Responsibilities

You will support senior executives and governance bodies by delivering rigorous, well-documented analysis, including:

Economic and financial analysis to support policy and program design decisions

Assessment of the impact of different fee structures against revenue assumptions

Analysis of operating model parameters and cost drivers

Scenario analysis for industrial settings, including wage and staffing variations

Evaluation of additional revenue sources, including Commonwealth Worker Retention Payments

Refinement and validation of assumptions in collaboration with financial modellers

Ensuring alignment with related business cases across government

Clear documentation of all assumption changes and impacts

Establishing mechanisms to monitor variance against the approved budget envelope and highlight emerging risks

Preparing briefing material and presenting findings to senior governance forums, including:

Program Control Groups

Program Implementation Committees

Executive and funding boards

Delivery Timeframes

This role is required immediately to support delivery against tight and critical milestones, including:

Full review of business case assumptions (mid-January)

Preliminary impact analysis for executive consideration (late January–February)

Final analysis to support key governance decisions (March)

Support for ERC submissions and callback processes (February–May)

About You

You are a senior analyst who combines technical depth with strong judgement and communication skills. You will bring:

Demonstrated experience as a Senior Policy Analyst, Economic Analyst or Financial Analyst in government or complex public-sector programs

Strong quantitative, economic and financial analysis capability

Experience working on business cases, funding submissions or ERC processes

Ability to translate complex financial modelling into clear, practical policy advice

Strong written skills, with experience producing executive-level briefs and decision papers

Confidence engaging with senior stakeholders and governance forums

Ability to work at pace, manage ambiguity and meet fixed deadlines

Apply now!

A unique opportunity to join Silverchain is now available as we progress our digital ambitions! As a Manager, Care Information and Engagment at Silverchain you'll be working within the Clinical Information & Engagment team and will lead the development and implementation of systems to improve care data collection, design, management, quality, governance and analytics capability across Silverchain.

What's on offer

Fulltime permanent role. Monday-Friday 76 hours per fortnight.
Hybrid role - working from home, flexible location VIC, WA, SA or NSW
Working for a non-profit organisation, you can salary package up to $18,500 tax free.
Everyday discounts, including discounted vouchers for Coles, Woolworths, Amazon, Myer, The Good Guys and more.
Comprehensive health and wellbeing resources and support.

What we're looking for

To thrive in this role you'll need to have:

Doctorate or Post Graduate qualification in health or social science, or significant equivalent experience in conducting data and information system development, analytics, system improvement and evaluation programs.
Significant health information management experience at senior level in healthcare or other public healthcare related industry.
Demonstrated substantial experience in the production of advanced reports to design and manage MDS requirements for the business.
Demonstrated interpersonal and communication skills (written, verbal and listening) to effectively consult with key stakeholders to gather requirements and present findings to a wide audience.
Demonstrated well developed conceptual, analytical skills and attention to detail.
Significant knowledge of the Community Care Data landscape with respect to variables, screening, assessment, patient reported measures and validated outcomes
Experience of presenting and discussing information to groups of stakeholders.

The role

As a Manager, Care Information and Engagement:

Create, manage and govern a Minimum Data Set (MDS) for Silverchain with an initial focus on care data.
Support the design, implementation process and ongoing management of the digital care systems (electronic care record, client relationship manager and others) by ensuring the MDS, client related data standards and data collection business rules are incorporated and regularly reviewed.
Ensure digital tools such as the electronic care record align with the MDS and participate in appropriate digital forums to achieve this
Coordinate the implementation and operation of the Care Documentation Governance system for Silverchain, working with research, safety and quality and clinical experts.
Provide leadership and advice in the key development areas of.
Costing of Care delivery (activity-based unit costing)
Development of measures of care, client outcomes, client demographics and client complexity
Development of measures, analytical approaches and reporting for Best Care outcomes and alignment with relevant standards
Development of measures, analysis and reporting for service delivery performance, research and innovation
Care data quality and data quality assurance activities
Champion the use of the MDS across the organisation and drive the concept that high quality data "is everyone's business.

Senior Data Analyst
 
Own the numbers that shape how a high-growth tech company scales.
 
In a nutshell
This is a senior, hands-on role for a data analyst who cares deeply about accuracy, clarity, and commercial impact. You'll own Removify's core metrics, dashboards, and reporting, creating a trusted source of truth that helps the business understand what's driving performance, where to focus, and what decisions actually matter.
 
We're a data-rich, operations-heavy business with proprietary systems, high volume, and global growth ambitions. This role isn't about producing more dashboards, it's about producing better insight, challenging assumptions, and making data genuinely useful as we scale.
 
If you enjoy translating messy, complex data into clear, actionable insight and aren't afraid to say "that metric won't help", this role is for you.
 
Why Removify?
Removify is a fast-growing digital reputation management company operating at scale across Australia, the US, and other global markets. We combine customer-facing products with complex internal operational systems that power how we deliver services at volume.
 
As the business has grown, so has the importance of our data. We sit on a unique mix of commercial, operational, and product data, creating real opportunities to improve performance, efficiency, and decision-making.
 
This is a chance to step into a senior, high-impact analytics role where your work directly influences how the business operates and scales.
 
What you'll be owning
You'll take full ownership of our core analytics layer, from definitions through to insight.
 
Metrics, Definitions & Source of Truth

Own and maintain the data dictionary and KPI definitions
Establish a single source of truth for business-critical metrics
Validate assumptions and ensure data accuracy and consistency
Dashboards & Reporting

Design, maintain, and rationalise dashboards across multiple BI tools
Organise reporting for clarity and usability, reducing noise, not adding to it
Ensure leaders trust the data they're using to make decisions
Insight & Analysis

Proactively analyse data to surface trends, drivers, risks, and opportunities
Translate vague or poorly formed requests into meaningful analysis
Explain why something matters, not just what happened
Commercial & Operational Understanding

Analyse revenue drivers, retention and churn, cost drivers, and operational throughput
Help the business understand efficiency, performance, and scale constraints
Partner with stakeholders to ensure insights are actionable and decision-led
Product & Customer Reporting

Work with Product and Technology teams to inform and improve customer-facing metrics and reports
Ensure external reporting is accurate, meaningful, and aligned with internal definitions
You'll work closely with the CEO and senior leaders and partner with experienced engineers who deeply understand our systems.
 
What we're looking for
You're a senior analyst who has worked in complex, commercial environments and understands the responsibility that comes with owning business-critical data. You're comfortable challenging requests, asking better questions, and prioritising insight over activity.
 
You care about correctness, context, and impact, and you want your work to actually influence decisions.
 
Must-haves

Strong SQL and data interrogation skills
Comfortable querying complex datasets and joining across multiple sources
Proven experience owning data dictionaries and metric definitions
Experience working across multiple BI or data visualisation tools, with deep expertise in at least one
Strong commercial and operational mindset (revenue, retention, costs, efficiency)
Ability to translate vague requests into clear, actionable insight
Confidence to challenge metrics and requests constructively
Focus on data accuracy, validation, and trust
Nice-to-haves

Experience in B2B, SaaS, subscription, or operations-heavy environments
Experience with services + software hybrid businesses
Familiarity with EOS scorecards or similar operating metrics
Light experience with data modelling or transformations (e.g. views, transformations)
Comfort using AI tools (e.g. ChatGPT) to accelerate analysis, validate logic, or explore insights
What this role is (and isn't)
This role is:

A senior ownership role with real influence on decision-making
A mix of analysis, insight, and stakeholder partnership
Focused on quality, clarity, and commercial impact
This role is not:

Pure data visualisation or vanity reporting
A purely academic or research-focused analytics role
A data engineering or infrastructure position
A role measured by dashboard count instead of decision impact
The perks

Salary range: $150,000 - $190,000 + super (depending on experience)
High-impact role in a fast-growing, high-volume business
Strong collaboration across Product, Tech, and Leadership
Modern office in Cremorne with great amenities (hybrid work arrangement, 1 day WFH optional for full-time)
Opportunity to shape how data is used as the business scales
Ready to make data matter?
If you're excited by the idea of owning core metrics, improving how decisions are made, and bringing clarity to a complex, high-growth environment, we'd love to hear from you.
 
Let's build the next chapter of Removify, together.

You will analyse past performance and forward-booking trends to inform pricing strategies, and you will implement price updates in the live system to execute ancillary pricing tests across markets.

You will work closely with the Ancillary Product, Distribution, Marketing, and Legal teams. Strong collaboration is essential, as design, messaging, and pricing all play a key role in the success and revenue performance of ancillary products.

You’ll be great in this role if you have: 

Bachelor's degree in a relevant field. 
Proven experience in analyzing complex data to derive meaningful insights and provide actionable recommendations. 
Proficiency in advanced Excel functions, Strong proficiency in SQL, and PowerBI for data analysis and visualization. 
Expertise in transforming business queries into analytical investigations to validate hypotheses. 
Outstanding communication skills, capable of articulating complex concepts and ideas clearly and effectively. 
Demonstrated ability to manage and engage stakeholders successfully. 
In-depth knowledge of the Australian aviation market. 

What you’ll get from us:

We’re committed to looking after you, with some of the best benefits and conditions in the industry – including (but not limited to)  

Discounted flights for you and your loved ones (including $1000 worth of travel credits per year)?  
A flexible, hybrid work style. Work from home or the office, adapt your location to suit your style and needs?  
One of Brisbane’s most admired head office locations, with South Bank train station, a supermarket, pharmacy, and lunch options downstairs plus a 5-minute walk to the Busway, a rooftop restaurant and onsite gym (with a low membership fee) and South Bank Parklands just across the road?  
Discounts on travel insurance, lounge membership, car hire, accommodation, and experiences worldwide?  
Cheaper hospitality, retail, technology, beauty and wellness services?  
Free counselling and access to a wellbeing app to support your physical, mental, social and financial health? 
‘Dress for Your Day’ – enjoy the freedom to wear whatever makes you feel great for the type of work you do and the day you have ahead of you.?  

When everyone is included, everyone wins 

We’re all individuals. And we love that. That’s why we encourage applications from Indigenous Australians, people with disability, those from diverse cultural backgrounds, our friends in the LGBTQI+ community, and anyone else who wants to join our family. 

Ready to apply?  

We’re ready to hear from you. Apply now.

The Company

Hypersonix is an Australian aerospace engineering and advanced manufacturing company building hydrogen-powered scramjet aircraft. We work at the bleeding edge of hypersonic technology, delivering aircraft that fly faster, reach further, and open new pathways to space.




The Role

As our FP&A Manager, you’ll drive financial planning, analysis, and decision support across a high-growth business. This is a leadership role partnering closely with senior executives and operational leaders to deliver accurate forecasting, insightful analysis, and data-driven recommendations that shape production, R&D programs, and revenue growth. Your expertise in financial modelling, budgeting, and scenario planning will help scale operations and support bold innovation.




Responsibilities

Lead annual budgeting and rolling forecast cycles.
Develop integrated financial models to support strategic decisions.
Build scenario and sensitivity analyses to support scaling.
Support pricing, margin, and cost build-ups for new programs and contracts.
Monthly management and Board level reporting with actionable insights.
Design KPIs and dashboards to monitor production, cost, delivery, and working capital performance.
Partner with Operations, Engineering, and Manufacturing to understand cost drivers and operational performance.
Monitor and forecast cash flow, including program-level impacts.
Build FP&A tools, models, and processes to support business scale and complexity.
Act as a trusted finance partner to senior leadership, providing strategic insights.

The Person

At Hypersonix, innovation isn’t just what we do—it’s who we are. We move fast, break boundaries, and redefine possibilities in aerospace. To succeed here, you’ll embrace change, stay resilient under pressure, and bring a proactive, solutions-focused mindset. If you’re adaptable, collaborative and thrive on challenges, this is your chance to make an impact.




Essential requirements

Degree in Accounting, Finance or a related field.
Professional certifications (IPA, CPA, CA, CIMA, ACCA).
5+ years in FP&A or strategic finance leadership roles.
Expertise in financial modelling, forecasting, and variance analysis.
Advanced Excel and proficiency in ERP systems and BI tools (Power BI, Tableau).
Strong business partnering and stakeholder management skills.
Eligible to obtain any required security clearance or background checks.
Right to live and work in Australia.

Desirable requirements

Experience within manufacturing, engineering, or aerospace industries (highly desirable).
Familiarity with Dynamics 365.
High-growth expertise.
Experience supporting capital raises, grants, and investor reporting.

Why Choose Hypersonix?

At Hypersonix, creativity meets cutting-edge technology. We value flexibility, collaboration, and continuous improvement, creating an environment where ideas turn into breakthroughs. You’ll work alongside passionate professionals delivering innovative solutions, where problem-solving, adaptability and excellence aren’t just expected—they’re celebrated. If you thrive on challenges and want to achieve the extraordinary, you’ll fit right in.




Benefits include:

Competitive salary and performance-based incentives.
Flexible working arrangements.
Inclusive, diverse and supportive team culture.
Career development and professional growth programs.
Free, confidential Employee Assistance Program.

With global partnerships, advanced manufacturing, and sustainable aerospace technology, Hypersonix is transforming the future of flight. Ready to accelerate your career and help shape the future of flight? Apply now and join us on the journey to Fly Faster.

Job Title: General Manager, Policy and Analysis Branch, Net Zero Economy Authority
Company: Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet
Ad Text:
Step into a pivotal leadership role as General Manager, Policy and Analysis with the Net Zero Economy Authority, where you’ll drive national policy and data strategy at the forefront of Australia’s economic and social transformation. This is your opportunity to shape the Authority’s policy agenda, lead high-performing teams, and deliver evidence-based insights that support workers, communities, and industries through the net zero transition. You’ll collaborate with senior officials, industry, and regional leaders, ensuring decisions are informed by robust analysis and innovative thinking. If you’re a strategic, values-driven leader with a passion for public sector impact and a commitment to building a better future, this high-profile executive position offers the chance to make a lasting difference.

Flexibility arrangements

Flexible work is a broad term used to describe a variety of different arrangements about how, when and where work is performed. The authority supports mutually beneficial flexible work arrangements which suit operational requirements. Arrangements may be consistent and regular, such as part time work, working from home a couple of days each week or remotely from another location; or more ad hoc such as varying work attendance times or occasional home based work. Consideration is given to all flexible work requests, approval is not limited to an employee’s classification level or caring responsibilities.

Eligibility

This role is being advertised as both ongoing and non-ongoing. The role may be offered as either ongoing or non-ongoing subject to business needs and/or candidate preference. Where a non-ongoing position is offered, the role will be filled as a specified term vacancy for an initial period of up to 12 months.
Under section 22(8) of the Public Service Act 1999, employees must be Australian citizens to be employed in the Australian Public Service (APS) unless the Agency Head has agreed otherwise, in writing. At NZEA (PM&C) to be eligible for this position you should be an Australian Citizen at the closing date of application, unless exceptional circumstances apply (see FAQs in the candidate information pack for more details).
Successful applicants will be required to undergo the process to obtain and maintain, or continue to hold the required security clearance level for the role as indicated. All NZEA staff are required to have a minimum baseline security clearance prior to commencement.
Successful applicants will be assessed through our pre-employment screening checks, including a Nationally Coordinated Criminal History Check, and will normally be subject to a six-month probation period if new to the APS, or if they have not yet completed their probation period elsewhere in the APS.

How to apply

If this sounds like the opportunity you are looking for, submit an online application through the Apply link by Sunday, 18 January 2026 at 11:30pm AEDT.

New year, new opportunity to grow your career in a dynamic and supportive multinational with excellent career progression!

About your new Employer!
  
This multinational, product-based organisation is a leader in its category across the APAC region. With strong year-on-year growth, complex operations and a genuinely collaborative culture, the business is investing heavily in commercial finance capability to support strategic decision-making. You’ll join a high-performing finance team that values curiosity, continuous improvement, and evidence-based insight. This is an environment where your recommendations influence senior leadership and directly shape future business outcomes.
  
About your new Role!
  
We’re looking for an experienced Finance Business Partner to step into a highly analytical, commercially impactful role with APAC-wide scope. Reporting directly to the CFO, you’ll work alongside multiple Finance Business Partners and will be the one who brings it all together. Your mandate is to take large volumes of operational and commercial data, analyse it, interpret it, and convert it into clear, actionable insights that support strategic and operational decision-making.
  
This role exists because the CFO needs more than just data, he needs meaningful stories, informed recommendations, and an ability to provide insights that influence business outcomes.
  
Key responsibilities include:

Business partnering across sales, operations, logistics and commercial teams
Analysing large datasets and distilling insights to support decision-making
Leading and coordinating the full planning process across APAC
Assessing the quality and reliability of sales forecasts and market assumptions
Supporting Sales & Operations Planning (S&OP) with commercial insight
CAPEX analysis, evaluation and recommendations
Identifying performance improvement opportunities and providing strategic suggestions
Storytelling: presenting insights in a compelling, logical, and impactful way
  
About You!

Professional qualification such as CA, CPA, CFA is desirable but not essential
3-5 years experience in a commercial role such as Finance Business Partner, Commercial Analyst, Commercial Manager
Highly analytical capability with experience working across large, complex datasets
Proven ability to convert numbers into commercial stories, insights and recommendations
Product based industry experience such as FMCG, Consumer Goods,  Manufacturing or similar is highly desirable
Strong understanding of planning cycles, forecasting and long-term modelling
Demonstrated ability to influence senior stakeholders and guide others through the planning process
Curious, commercially minded and proactive; constantly questioning how performance can be improved
Exceptional communication and stakeholder engagement skills
  
What’s in it for You?

Circa. $160,000 – $175,000 base + super + bonus
High-impact role with direct influence on APAC strategy
Work closely with a commercial, forward-thinking CFO
Clear and tangible career progression opportunities
Collaborative culture with strong executive exposure
Hybrid working arrangement | Close to Public Transport
Please APPLY NOW or contact Declan Stacey on 0483 945 773 for more information.

Binance is a leading global blockchain ecosystem behind the world’s largest cryptocurrency exchange by trading volume and registered users. We are trusted by over 280 million people in 100+ countries for our industry-leading security, user fund transparency, trading engine speed, deep liquidity, and an unmatched portfolio of digital-asset products. Binance offerings range from trading and finance to education, research, payments, institutional services, Web3 features, and more. We leverage the power of digital assets and blockchain to build an inclusive financial ecosystem to advance the freedom of money and improve financial access for people around the world.

We are looking for a Data Scientist expert to drive advancements in natural language processing and computer vision. You’ll work across content understanding scenarios such as classification, entity recognition, sentiment analysis, and image/video understanding, and help build large-scale systems that power content moderation, recommendation, and search.

Develop and optimize NLP/CV algorithms to improve the performance and efficiency of content understanding pipelines.
Build scalable models (e.g., BERT, GPT, ViT, CLIP) and bring them into production.
Partner with product and data teams to diagnose business challenges and design data-driven solutions.
Track cutting-edge research and explore novel algorithms for real-world applications in content understanding.
Drive system improvements that enhance moderation, recommendation and search workflow
Master’s Degree or above in Computer Science, AI, EE, Mathematics, or related fields.
Strong programming skills in Python or C++ and familiarity with deep learning frameworks such as PyTorch.
Solid foundation in machine learning/deep learning and hands-on experience with common models in NLP and/or CV.
Experience working with large-scale data processing frameworks (Hadoop/Spark/Flink is a plus).
2+ years of algorithm/model development experience.
Background in content safety, recommendation or search systems is highly valued.

Why Binance

• Shape the future with the world’s leading blockchain ecosystem

• Collaborate with world-class talent in a user-centric global organization with a flat structure

• Tackle unique, fast-paced projects with autonomy in an innovative environment

• Thrive in a results-driven workplace with opportunities for career growth and continuous learning

• Competitive salary and company benefits

• Work-from-home arrangement (the arrangement may vary depending on the work nature of the business team)
